Kibo Energy has been informed by Mbeya Power that its Water Rights, acquired during August 2018, were successfully renewed ahead of schedule. This ensures that the Mbeya Coal to Power Project (MCPP) EIA certification remains valid and maintains the right to use large quantities of water, a strategic commodity for the MCPP, specifically by the Power Station. Read more about East Africa Louis Coetzee, CEO of Kibo, comments, “I am very encouraged by the overall progress being made at MCCP. "The renewal of the Water Permits, so soon after the recent approval and processing of seven Mining Rights for the Project, further confirms my confidence in its potential.” 